Description

[Migr-ai-tion.net]Â is
an applied, interdisciplinary
research project that investiga-
tes the potentials of AI as a partici-
patory and therapeutic medium to work
with the digital diaspora. Situated at the
nexus of migration studies, media and future
anthropology and speculative design, the
project tackles issues such as data
colonialism in computer vision,
stereotypes, marginalisation, collective
trauma and agency.

The platform will collect and
map a collaborative image dataset, uploaded by users
worldwide for training future computer vision techno-
logies challenging mainstream representations
of migrant experiences.
